---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';

const hSystem =
	'border-b border-neutral-800/35 pb-6 text-lg font-bold uppercase tracking-[0.14em] text-cyan-300/82 md:text-xl';
const pBody = 'mt-8 text-sm leading-relaxed text-neutral-400';
---

<Layout title="System Architecture · Empyrria Sigil Codex" currentPath={Astro.url.pathname}>
	<main class="mx-auto max-w-2xl px-6 py-12 md:px-8 md:py-16">
		<p class="text-[0.65rem] font-medium uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-neutral-500">Codex</p>
		<h1
			class="mt-3 text-[2.125rem] font-semibold tracking-tight text-neutral-50 md:text-[2.75rem] md:leading-[1.08]"
		>
			System Architecture
		</h1>

		<p class="mt-4 max-w-2xl text-base leading-relaxed text-neutral-400 md:text-[1.0625rem]">
			Empyrria is not a collection of symbols. It is a structured system where each element has a defined role.
		</p>

		<section class="mt-12 space-y-12 md:mt-14" aria-label="Layers">
			<div>
				<h2 class={hSystem}>Core of Being</h2>
				<p class={pBody}>The Core defines identity. It does not change. It cannot be replaced.</p>
				<p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-relaxed text-neutral-400">
					It determines resonance, direction, and the fundamental reason an entity acts.
				</p>
			</div>

			<div>
				<h2 class={hSystem}>Doctrine</h2>
				<p class={pBody}>Doctrine defines structure and truth. It exists independently of individuals.</p>
				<p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-relaxed text-neutral-400">
					It acts as a stabilizing layer that gives meaning direction and limits.
				</p>
			</div>

			<div>
				<h2 class={hSystem}>State</h2>
				<p class={pBody}>
					A state is an alignment condition. It is trainable, temporary, and dependent on discipline.
				</p>
				<p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-relaxed text-neutral-400">
					It determines how power is applied, not what that power is.
				</p>
			</div>

			<div>
				<h2 class={hSystem}>Discipline</h2>
				<p class={pBody}>Discipline defines execution. It is the learned method through which actions are performed.</p>
			</div>

			<div>
				<h2 class={hSystem}>Phenomenon</h2>
				<p class={pBody}>Phenomena are system events. They are not chosen, but experienced.</p>
			</div>

			<div>
				<h2 class={hSystem}>Sigil</h2>
				<p class={pBody}>A sigil is the symbolic layer. It represents and stabilizes elements of the system.</p>
			</div>

			<div>
				<h2 class={hSystem}>Command / War</h2>
				<p class={pBody}>Command aligns multiple entities under a shared intent.</p>
				<p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-relaxed text-neutral-400">
					It transforms individual alignment into collective action.
				</p>
			</div>
		</section>

		<div
			class="mt-12 rounded-lg border border-neutral-800/70 border-l-cyan-950/80 bg-neutral-900/25 px-5 py-6 text-sm leading-relaxed text-cyan-200/55 md:px-6"
		>
			The system only works when these layers remain aligned. Power without alignment leads to collapse. Alignment
			allows power to remain stable.
		</div>

		<nav class="mt-10 flex flex-col gap-4 border-t border-neutral-800/60 pt-10 text-sm" aria-label="Continue">
			<a
				href="/codex"
				class="text-neutral-400 underline-offset-4 transition-colors hover:text-neutral-200 hover:underline focus-visible:outline focus-visible:outline-2 focus-visible:outline-offset-2 focus-visible:outline-neutral-500/40"
			>
				← Codex hub
			</a>
			<a
				href="/codex/what-is-a-sigil"
				class="text-neutral-400 underline-offset-4 transition-colors hover:text-amber-200/90 hover:underline focus-visible:outline focus-visible:outline-2 focus-visible:outline-offset-2 focus-visible:outline-amber-500/35"
			>
				← What is a Sigil
			</a>
			<a
				href="/showcase"
				class="text-neutral-400 underline-offset-4 transition-colors hover:text-neutral-200 hover:underline focus-visible:outline focus-visible:outline-2 focus-visible:outline-offset-2 focus-visible:outline-neutral-500/40"
			>
				→ Showcase
			</a>
		</nav>
	</main>
</Layout>
